questions page 10-15:
1. How did the mother feel about their collecting toothpaste tubes? Provide reference
Annoyed and fed up with the growing mess. Reference :“My mom grew distressed… ‘Do something with this mess or I’m going to throw it out.’” (p. 23)
2. Which of the two fathers drove up with a friend?
The narrator’s own father (TPD). 
Reference : “One day my dad drove up with a friend…” (p. 24)
! because the scene happens at the narrator’s house and ‘my dad’ always means his biological father in that chapter.
3. How did he feel when he first saw the production line?
Cautious and concerned about what the boys were doing
reference : “Dad walked up cautiously…” (p. 24)
4. How did he feel after he understood what the boys were doing?
Surprised, amused, proud
reference : “My dad smiled and shook his head… ‘You boys have shown great creativity… I’m really proud of you.’” (p. 25)
5. Did people often frequent Mike’s house, according to the author? Provide reference
Yes. Mike’s house was very busy because of his father’s employees
Reference : The author asks: “Who are those people?” -> construction supervisor…” (p. 27)
6. How did the author feel when he visited Mike’s house?
Uncomfortable and claustrophobic. 
Reference : “I felt claustrophobic as I entered the narrow living room.”   (p. 27)
7. What was the difference in the two dads’ first appearance? (not the look, but how they were first mentioned)
Their mode of introduction. One father appeared directly in action, while the other was introduced indirectly through others before appearing.
Reference : Poor dad: “My dad put down the evening paper…” (p. 21)
